<h1>INC Election Manifesto</h1><br>
<p>
<h2 style="font-weight:bold">1.  ECONOMIC GROWTH</h2>
8% plus growth rate within three years. Zero aversion to foreign investment. Our “Direct Tax Code” and the “GST” Bill’s will increase aggregate revenue. Our “Jobs Agenda” will create 10 crore new jobs.<br><br>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold">2.  PROTECTING THE INTERESTS OF LABOUR</h2>
Health and pension cover for the entire labour class. All migrant labour will be brought under the Aadhaar programme, within a year. Special focus on labour working in high risk industries and plantations.<br><br>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold">3.  RIGHT TO HEALTH</h2>
Universal “Right to Health”. Healthcare vans will reach every part of India. We will strengthen infrastructure and increase health expenditure to 3% of GDP. 60 lakh new jobs in health sector by 2020.<br><br>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold">4.  EMPOWERING SCHEDULED CASTES, SCHEDULED TRIBES AND OTHER BACKWARD CLASSES</h2>
Assured education and employment for SCs, STs and OBCs, through reservation. Skill development vouchers and schools in every block. Affirmative action for SCs and STs in private sector.<br><br>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold">5.  WOMEN’S EMPOWERMENT AND PROTECTION OF CHILDREN</h2>
Our “Women's Reservation Bill” will secure 33% of seats in Parliament for women. Fast track courts for women’s issues. 30% of all Panchayat and Nagarpalika funds for women and child development.<br><br>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold">6.  SAFEGUARDING MINORITIES</h2>
Equal space for minorities in India. We are committed to fighting communalism by enacting the “Communal Violence Bill”. Easy access to credit and other incentives like tax rebates. Reservation in government jobs.<br><br>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold">7.  YOUTH AND STUDENT AGENDA</h2>
Quality education and sports infrastructure in India. A National Sports Education University will nurture talent. We will address issues relating to discrimination against students from the North East and J&K.<br><br>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold">8.  RURAL DEVELOPMENT AND PANCHAYATI RAJ</h2>
Universal pension scheme for the elderly, widows and similar groups. 100% digitisation of rural land records. Food security schemes will be expanded to include subsidised pulses and cooking oil.<br><br>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold">9.  AGRICULTURE AND FARMER WELFARE</h2>
FDI in multi-brand retail will bring better returns to farmers. Lower interest rates for farmers. Increased spending on agricultural education. Addition of 1 crore hectares to total irrigated area.<br><br>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold">10. ACCELERATING INDUSTRIAL AND MANUFACTURING GROWTH</h2>
Our “National Manufacturing Policy” will ensure manufacturing sector’s share of GDP increases to 25% by 2022. Completion of industrial corridors will catalyse economic growth. SME’s will have access to world-class technology at affordable costs.<br><br>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold">11. INFRASTRUCTURE</h2>
$1 trillion for upgrading infrastructure. Connecting all million-plus cities by High Speed Rail. Completion of the Western and Eastern Dedicated Freight Corridors. New infrastructure for air travel across the country.<br><br>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold">12. URBAN DEVELOPMENT</h2>
Mayors and Municipal Chairpersons will operate as CEOs with executive powers and responsibilities. We will create 100 new urban clusters around small and emerging cities and link them with power and transport facilities.<br><br>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold">13. HOUSING</h2>
Universal “Right to Homestead”. Affordable and quality housing for all. Rajiv Awaas Yojana and Indira Awaas Yojana will be expanded to cover all poor households in urban and rural India.<br><br>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold">14. ENVIRONMENT</h2>
Ensure sustainable development in its true spirit. Rigorous environmental appraisals. Launch of “Green National Accounts” will ensure costs of environmental degradation are clearly reflected in India’s national accounts.<br><br>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold">15. INNOVATION, INFORMATION AND COMMUNICATION TECHNOLOGY</h2>
Ensure passage of the “Electronic Delivery of Service Bill, 2011” and work towards effectively delivering all public services like ration cards, electronically. Connect all 2.5 lakh Gram Panchayats with high-speed broadband.<br><br>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold">16. FIGHTING CORRUPTION</h2>
We will enact the anti-graft Bills that were stalled by the opposition. Ensure serious and systematic efforts to recover black money and a Special Envoy to pursue this agenda.<br><br>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold">17. GOVERNANCE REFORMS</h2>
Transparency in financing of political activities. Expansion of state funding for elections. A law to decriminalise consensual sexual relations between same-sex adults. “Judicial Appointments Bill” to ensure transparency in appointment of judges.<br><br>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold">18. INTERNAL SECURITY</h2>
Address the challenges of Left Wing Extremism. Ensure that our police forces are equipped with modern weapons and technology. Development agenda to empower the people in LWE affected areas will continue.<br><br>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold">19. DEFENCE AND WELFARE OF EX-SERVICEMEN</h2>
Ensure a transparent process of procuring state-of-the-art equipment. Fresh impetus to upgrading domestic manufacturing capabilities. Ensure welfare of Ex-Servicemen by establishing a “National Commission for Ex-Servicemen”.<br><br>

<h2 style="font-weight:bold">20. FOREIGN POLICY</h2>
Fight terrorism through greater intelligence sharing and cooperation with countries. Continue our humanitarian and developmental assistance to Tamil-speaking people in Sri Lanka. Mobilize support for India's permanent membership in the UN Security Council.<br><br>

